WEBVTT

00:07.137 --> 00:07.355
.

00:07.398 --> 00:09.487
[tense music]

00:09.531 --> 00:15.145
♪

00:15.189 --> 00:17.669
- Here to see Walker North.
- ID.

00:19.541 --> 00:21.456
ID.

00:28.245 --> 00:31.161
Secure your service weapon.

00:36.384 --> 00:37.776
[elevator dings]

00:37.820 --> 00:44.827
♪

00:55.359 --> 00:56.491
- [sighs]

01:03.411 --> 01:06.109
- Sergeant Voight, Special
Agent North will see you now.

01:06.153 --> 01:07.458
- Thank you.

01:14.770 --> 01:17.381
Thank you.
- Have a seat.

01:17.425 --> 01:19.731
Oh. I'm sorry, man.

01:19.775 --> 01:22.169
I told 'em to park you in here,
where you'd be more comfy,

01:22.212 --> 01:25.128
but these people.

01:25.172 --> 01:27.391
This place is run by cadavers.
[both chuckle]

01:27.435 --> 01:30.438
"Bureaucrats" as they're known
in the wild.

01:30.481 --> 01:34.311
- Agent North.
What can I do for you?

01:43.886 --> 01:45.714
- Roy Walton.

01:49.283 --> 01:51.198
One sick man.

01:51.241 --> 01:53.243
Drug trafficking,
human trafficking,

01:53.287 --> 01:55.593
killed three girls,
tried to kill a cop,

01:55.637 --> 01:58.596
and then he just disappeared.

01:58.640 --> 01:59.902
- [grunts]

02:01.686 --> 02:02.948
- When it all went down,

02:02.992 --> 02:05.777
your deputy supe, Sam Miller--
you know Sam?

02:05.821 --> 02:07.431
- Yes.

02:07.475 --> 02:10.608
- Well, Sam wanted fresh eyes
on the case,

02:10.652 --> 02:13.568
and our assumption was--
and yours too, I believe--

02:13.611 --> 02:15.657
is that Roy Walton
left the city.

02:15.700 --> 02:18.268
- That's right.

02:18.312 --> 02:22.229
- Well, turns out he didn't.

02:22.272 --> 02:25.623
Walton never left Chicago.
- Huh.

02:26.972 --> 02:28.887
- After it all went down,
Walton had his cousin buy him

02:28.931 --> 02:30.280
a ticket up to Grand Rapids.

02:30.324 --> 02:31.890
He never got on the train.

02:31.934 --> 02:35.851
And we combed through every
camera on every traffic light,

02:35.894 --> 02:40.464
toll booth, you know, planes,
trains, automobiles--bupkes.

02:40.508 --> 02:43.293
- People don't just disappear.
- [chuckles]

02:43.337 --> 02:44.990
That's right.

02:45.034 --> 02:46.644
No, Roy's here somewhere.

02:46.688 --> 02:50.213
♪

02:50.257 --> 02:53.390
Look, I know this was
a tough case for your guys.

02:53.434 --> 02:54.652
You almost lost one
of your own?

02:54.696 --> 02:57.481
- We did.

02:57.525 --> 03:00.310
- I got no interest in scraping
off fresh scabs here,

03:00.354 --> 03:04.358
but I got to put together
a precise timeline for Walton.

03:04.401 --> 03:06.534
- You need our files,
no problem.

03:06.577 --> 03:09.754
- That's--and--and I need
to talk with your guys too.

03:09.798 --> 03:10.886
- [grunts]
- Uh, you're with

03:10.929 --> 03:13.323
the Intelligence Unit?
[phone buzzes]

03:13.367 --> 03:16.021
Right?
You--you work out of the 21st?

03:16.065 --> 03:18.459
That's West Side?

03:18.502 --> 03:21.984
- Southeast, low end.

03:22.027 --> 03:25.335
Listen, my unit's responding
to a scene right now.

03:25.379 --> 03:28.251
- Do your thing, please.
Uh, that's all, really.

03:28.295 --> 03:31.472
- Listen, we're an open book,
so anything you need.

03:31.515 --> 03:33.430
- Much appreciated.

03:33.474 --> 03:40.481
♪

03:49.316 --> 03:51.970
- Chicago PD!
- Here!

03:52.014 --> 03:54.321
- You clear the house yet?
- No.

03:54.364 --> 03:56.540
Riding solo, been with him.
Guy with a knife--

03:56.584 --> 03:58.716
20s, Hispanic, gangbanger,
his words.

03:58.760 --> 03:59.761
- [gurgling]
Please.

03:59.804 --> 04:01.806
Just take care of my girls.

04:01.850 --> 04:05.462
- Hailey, I'm going upstairs.
- Yeah, I got down here.

04:05.506 --> 04:12.513
♪

04:18.519 --> 04:20.564
- Hailey, I got blood upstairs.
It started here.

04:20.608 --> 04:21.783
I'm clearing the rest
of the floor.

04:26.701 --> 04:28.920
- Chicago Police!
I know you're in there.

04:28.964 --> 04:31.749
Come out with your hands up
or I will assume

04:31.793 --> 04:32.968
that you're armed.

04:35.449 --> 04:36.711
- [screaming]
No!

04:36.754 --> 04:37.973
No! Please.

04:38.016 --> 04:40.323
- Okay, okay! It's okay.

04:40.367 --> 04:41.759
You're okay, you're okay.

04:41.803 --> 04:43.848
- [panting]

04:43.892 --> 04:45.197
Dad! Where's my dad?

04:45.241 --> 04:47.112
- We're getting him help.
All right, it's okay.

04:47.156 --> 04:48.810
- [sobs]

04:52.814 --> 04:55.730
- Heard screaming.
It was bad.

04:55.773 --> 04:58.428
I called 911.

04:58.472 --> 04:59.777
He isn't okay, is he?

04:59.821 --> 05:01.692
- We're doing everything
we can for him, ma'am.

05:01.736 --> 05:04.826
- Harvey's a good father,
a good man.

05:04.869 --> 05:06.567
- All right.
Well, thank you.

05:10.135 --> 05:11.311
How's the kid?

05:11.354 --> 05:13.965
- I don't know,
still trying to breathe.

05:14.009 --> 05:15.489
- What do we got?

05:15.532 --> 05:17.621
- Harvey Clarke, 44,
multiple stab wounds,

05:17.665 --> 05:19.406
back, torso--on his way to Med.

05:19.449 --> 05:20.929
- Sounds like home invasion
gone wrong.

05:20.972 --> 05:22.974
Clarke said a guy busted
in the side door,

05:23.018 --> 05:24.802
went for his late wife's
jewelry.

05:24.846 --> 05:26.978
Described him as a thin,
young Hispanic male.

05:27.022 --> 05:28.763
- Clarke lives here
with his two daughters.

05:28.806 --> 05:31.896
The one I found, Candace,
she's 14 years old.

05:31.940 --> 05:33.855
And there's an older one,
Darlene,

05:33.898 --> 05:35.378
16, went to school early,

05:35.422 --> 05:36.727
probably has no idea
this ever happened.

05:36.771 --> 05:38.468
- Well,
you got Social Services on her?

05:38.512 --> 05:39.991
- Yeah, they're taking 'em
to their grandmother's house.

05:40.035 --> 05:42.385
It's the only local relative.
- What about their mother?

05:42.429 --> 05:44.039
- She passed away.

05:44.082 --> 05:46.520
- Neighbor said it was some
sort of autoimmune thing.

05:46.563 --> 05:48.478
- Sarge!
- What do you got?

05:48.522 --> 05:50.393
- All right, so we found
two cash counters

05:50.437 --> 05:52.090
and a bag of rubber bands
in the garage,

05:52.134 --> 05:53.831
which means that whatever
our victim does,

05:53.875 --> 05:55.224
he does it in cash.

05:55.267 --> 05:58.140
But Sarge, there's no sign
of forced entry at all,

05:58.183 --> 05:59.620
which means
that whoever did this

05:59.663 --> 06:00.882
possibly just walked right in.

06:00.925 --> 06:02.449
Maybe they had a key
or the door was open,

06:02.492 --> 06:04.102
but I think that's worth
asking some questions.

06:04.146 --> 06:06.409
- Yeah, like,
maybe the offender knew him.

06:06.453 --> 06:07.497
Chase it.
- Copy that.

06:07.541 --> 06:09.107
- All right,
I want to work this wide.

06:09.151 --> 06:11.458
Have Forensics dust
the whole house for prints.

06:11.501 --> 06:13.721
Adam, look for patterns
of break-ins,

06:13.764 --> 06:15.026
known burglars in the area.

06:15.070 --> 06:17.551
Jay, Hailey,

06:17.594 --> 06:20.597
meet me two blocks east
in five.

06:20.641 --> 06:23.600
[suspenseful music]

06:23.644 --> 06:25.428
♪

06:25.472 --> 06:26.908
- The FBI has
an active investigation

06:26.951 --> 06:29.214
into the disappearance
of Roy Walton?

06:29.258 --> 06:30.564
- You told us they weren't
gonna do anything more

06:30.607 --> 06:32.087
than put his picture
up in the post office.

06:32.130 --> 06:33.654
We're talking about the end
of our careers,

06:33.697 --> 06:35.656
disbanding of the whole unit,

06:35.699 --> 06:36.613
prison.

06:38.223 --> 06:40.835
- They have nothing.
It's a fishing expedition.

06:40.878 --> 06:42.880
- You believe that?

06:42.924 --> 06:44.142
- Well, if they have anything
more than nothing,

06:44.186 --> 06:45.970
I'll find out.

06:48.016 --> 06:49.887
Look, if we stick together...

06:54.936 --> 06:56.198
We're fine.

07:00.942 --> 07:02.639
All right, where are we?

07:02.683 --> 07:03.901
- Victim's not out
of the woods yet.

07:03.945 --> 07:06.469
One of the stab wounds
lacerated his liver.

07:06.513 --> 07:08.079
- We did our due diligence
on the guy.

07:08.123 --> 07:09.777
Found some chinks in the armor,

07:09.820 --> 07:12.519
some, uh,
happenings with his business.

07:12.562 --> 07:16.740
- Everyone, this is
Agent Walker North, FBI.

07:16.784 --> 07:19.221
He's leading the investigation
into Roy Walton.

07:19.264 --> 07:21.658
He's gonna be hanging
around a bit.

07:21.702 --> 07:23.530
- Hey, come on in, Agent North.

07:23.573 --> 07:24.574
Pulled all our files,

07:24.618 --> 07:25.923
got you set up
right over there.

07:25.967 --> 07:28.186
- Ah. Yeah, careful.

07:28.230 --> 07:30.232
I might never leave.

07:30.275 --> 07:32.887
- So look, Agent North
is gonna be speaking to each

07:32.930 --> 07:34.279
of you over the next few days,

07:34.323 --> 07:36.586
figuring out if Roy Walton
might have gotten away.

07:36.630 --> 07:38.153
- This is all routine.

07:41.635 --> 07:44.072
Kim Burgess?

07:44.115 --> 07:47.989
- That's me.
- Thank you for your sacrifice.

07:48.032 --> 07:50.121
I'm not gonna stop
until I find Walton.

07:50.165 --> 07:51.122
- Please don't.

07:51.166 --> 07:52.297
I want to pitch in,

07:52.341 --> 07:54.169
so anything you need,
I'm here to help.

07:56.214 --> 07:57.607
- Hey, you guys--
you guys were up

07:57.651 --> 07:59.000
to some real police work here.

07:59.043 --> 08:00.610
Please, carry on.
- All right, you heard the man.

08:00.654 --> 08:02.220
Let's go.
- All right, Harvey Clarke owns

08:02.264 --> 08:03.744
two nightclubs
in Little Village.

08:03.787 --> 08:06.616
Both are lowbrow dives.

08:06.660 --> 08:09.619
- And according to a civil case
a customer filed

08:09.663 --> 08:12.143
against Clarke,
this is his head of security,

08:12.187 --> 08:13.971
Lorenzo Santiago, 26 years old.

08:14.015 --> 08:15.712
- Right, and that's
the soft complication.

08:15.756 --> 08:17.671
He's also a documented
shot-caller

08:17.714 --> 08:19.977
in the local neighborhood gang,
Los Guerreros.

08:20.021 --> 08:21.283
- We've got
numerous phone calls

08:21.326 --> 08:22.632
between Santiago and Clarke.

08:22.676 --> 08:25.026
GPS puts Santiago
at the Clarke residence

08:25.069 --> 08:27.550
two days before the stabbing,
multiple times before that.

08:27.594 --> 08:30.988
- Yeah, well, if Clarke knows
this guy Santiago,

08:31.032 --> 08:32.599
why not just ID him himself?

08:32.642 --> 08:34.601
- No way of asking
for another 24 hours.

08:34.644 --> 08:36.690
Clarke's in an induced coma.

08:36.733 --> 08:38.605
- Well, we still got plenty
of probable cause.

08:38.648 --> 08:40.041
Bring him in.

08:51.792 --> 08:54.838
- There.
Blue plaid shirt and jeans.

08:54.882 --> 08:57.624
- We got a positive ID
on Lorenzo Santiago.

08:57.667 --> 09:00.670
[unsettling music]

09:00.714 --> 09:02.237
- We're moving too.

09:02.280 --> 09:08.939
♪

09:13.117 --> 09:15.903
- Lorenzo Santiago!
Chicago PD!

09:15.946 --> 09:16.991
- [grunts]

09:17.034 --> 09:19.994
[tense music]

09:20.037 --> 09:21.648
♪

09:21.691 --> 09:24.172
- Stop!

09:24.215 --> 09:25.347
[glass shatters]
[person yelps]

09:25.390 --> 09:26.870
10-1, 10-1.
Shots fired at the police.

09:26.914 --> 09:27.958
- Get down, get down!
- Move!

09:28.002 --> 09:29.220
Get out of the way!
- Get down!

09:34.443 --> 09:37.881
- He's headed for the roof.
- I got the back.

09:44.018 --> 09:45.933
Gunner's moving westbound
on the roof.

09:53.157 --> 09:54.855
- Stop!

09:59.337 --> 10:02.166
Drop it! Drop it!

10:02.210 --> 10:09.217
♪

10:11.045 --> 10:12.220
- Offender's hanging
from the roof,

10:12.263 --> 10:14.091
northwest corner, roll an ambo.

10:14.135 --> 10:16.398
- Drop the gun,
I'll pull you up.

10:16.441 --> 10:18.792
Or you are on your own.

10:18.835 --> 10:21.664
Either you're gonna fall,
or we're gonna shoot you.

10:21.708 --> 10:24.145
You're dead either way.

10:24.188 --> 10:25.799
Listen to what I'm saying
to you!

10:31.935 --> 10:35.330
- His name is Harvey Clarke.

10:35.373 --> 10:37.854
- Never seen him.
- Oh, really?

10:37.898 --> 10:40.074
'Cause that is damn sure
you working the door

10:40.117 --> 10:42.250
at his nightclub.

10:42.293 --> 10:43.381
I got you on two counts

10:43.425 --> 10:45.122
attempted murder
of a police officer.

10:45.166 --> 10:48.169
You got one shot at ever
seeing daylight again.

10:51.172 --> 10:53.435
So?

10:53.478 --> 10:55.437
- Look, I didn't run from y'all
because of Harvey Clarke.

10:55.480 --> 10:57.787
- No, you ran because
you thought the bill was due

10:57.831 --> 10:59.441
for running a gang.

10:59.484 --> 11:01.878
Harvey Clarke.
- Look, I know him.

11:01.922 --> 11:04.141
I work with him, but I didn't
bust into his house

11:04.185 --> 11:05.882
and stab him!

11:05.926 --> 11:09.190
- Well, I can put you
at his house two days ago,

11:09.233 --> 11:12.062
right before somebody put
a knife in his liver.

11:12.106 --> 11:15.065
[suspenseful music]

11:15.109 --> 11:22.072
♪

11:22.116 --> 11:24.161
Look.

11:24.205 --> 11:26.076
Okay.

11:26.120 --> 11:30.951
I go to Harvey's once a week
to drop off cash.

11:32.517 --> 11:34.345
We use the sales that we make
on the street

11:34.389 --> 11:37.044
to wash money
from his nightclubs.

11:37.087 --> 11:40.134
- Clarke is involved
in narcotics?

11:40.177 --> 11:42.223
- No. Just skimping on taxes.

11:46.793 --> 11:49.273
- You can try and talk to them,
but they're barely speaking.

11:49.317 --> 11:51.362
- Has your office had contact
with the family before?

11:51.406 --> 11:53.538
- No.
DCFS has never been called.

11:53.582 --> 11:56.019
Seem like a good family.
That's them.

11:58.152 --> 11:59.762
- Thank you.

12:03.157 --> 12:07.378
Darlene, you were already gone
for the day, right?

12:07.422 --> 12:10.120
- Marching band
just started up again.

12:10.164 --> 12:13.210
Practice
is before first period.

12:13.254 --> 12:16.953
- And Candace, you were--
- About to leave for school.

12:16.997 --> 12:19.260
Heard Dad yelling upstairs
with a man.

12:19.303 --> 12:21.392
- Did you see this man come in?

12:21.436 --> 12:23.307
- No.

12:23.351 --> 12:26.006
Just heard them.

12:26.049 --> 12:28.399
[sighs]
Then I heard Dad scream.

12:28.443 --> 12:31.054
- And that's when you hid
in the pantry?

12:31.098 --> 12:32.969
- [sniffles]
Yeah.

12:33.013 --> 12:34.536
I should have been more brave.

12:34.579 --> 12:36.494
- You were plenty brave.

12:36.538 --> 12:40.150
♪

12:40.194 --> 12:42.109
- I'm Emily Roberts,
one of the doctors

12:42.152 --> 12:43.806
that's been caring
for your father.

12:43.850 --> 12:46.200
- Is he gonna be okay?

12:46.243 --> 12:47.897
- No, girls, he's not.

12:47.941 --> 12:51.118
I'm sorry.
There was just too much damage.

12:51.161 --> 12:53.555
- [sobbing]

12:53.598 --> 12:55.078
- I'm so sorry.

12:55.122 --> 12:58.125
[somber music]

12:58.168 --> 13:02.433
♪

13:22.366 --> 13:22.540
.

13:22.584 --> 13:25.413
- Hey.

13:25.456 --> 13:28.677
You gonna tell me why you
asked me to pull all this info?

13:28.720 --> 13:30.679
- You don't want me
to tell you.

13:33.116 --> 13:34.465
What'd you find?

13:34.509 --> 13:36.206
- Nothing good.

13:36.250 --> 13:39.122
Agent North's routine
about not knowing where we work

13:39.166 --> 13:40.341
or what we do for a living.

13:40.384 --> 13:41.995
- That's a front.

13:42.038 --> 13:44.475
- He already pulled
everything weeks ago.

13:44.519 --> 13:48.566
Personnel files, financials,
psych, every beef, every arrest

13:48.610 --> 13:50.394
for everyone that works
in Intelligence.

13:50.438 --> 13:53.615
This dude might as well
be crashing on your couch.

13:53.658 --> 13:55.747
- He texted me.

13:55.791 --> 13:59.534
And he's starting to interview
our guys now, Trudy.

14:01.492 --> 14:03.190
I got to know what he knows.

14:03.233 --> 14:06.193
[tense music]

14:06.236 --> 14:11.111
♪

14:11.154 --> 14:12.329
- I should be dead.

14:14.418 --> 14:17.030
So yeah,
that's a weird way to live.

14:18.466 --> 14:19.597
- Hmm.
[clicks tongue]

14:19.641 --> 14:21.077
How did it start?

14:21.121 --> 14:22.557
- We split up searching
for Walton.

14:22.600 --> 14:24.776
- Holding anchor
at one location.

14:24.820 --> 14:26.735
- Officer Burgess,
she wound up alone.

14:26.778 --> 14:28.606
- I found her vehicle
unoccupied.

14:28.650 --> 14:30.347
- We've all had our share
of rough days.

14:30.391 --> 14:32.523
- That was a real tough day.
- It was a failure.

14:32.567 --> 14:35.091
- Knowing Roy Walton
is still out there...

14:35.135 --> 14:36.701
- We're not used to not getting
our man around here.

14:36.745 --> 14:38.703
We would have run through
a wall to find her that day.

14:38.747 --> 14:41.184
- Situations like that,
it can feel so desperate,

14:41.228 --> 14:42.533
sometimes it's tempting

14:42.577 --> 14:44.144
for cops to take things
into their own hands.

14:44.187 --> 14:46.320
- Sometimes.
- But in the end,

14:46.363 --> 14:49.410
it was good old-fashioned,
textbook cop work

14:49.453 --> 14:51.281
that brought Kim Burgess home.

14:51.325 --> 14:53.109
- Then we had to find the son
of a bitch who shot her.

14:53.153 --> 14:55.285
- Here's where the thing
makes you crazy.

14:55.329 --> 14:57.766
- We had him.
- Then we didn't.

15:00.508 --> 15:04.338
- I can recreate the movements
for the whole team that night,

15:04.381 --> 15:06.427
but not you.

15:08.820 --> 15:10.779
Do you remember Mark Irwin?

15:17.177 --> 15:19.919
Your street notes say
that Mark Irwin was suspected

15:19.962 --> 15:23.270
of helping Roy Walton disappear
that night.

15:23.313 --> 15:25.141
- Yep.
- And you were supposed

15:25.185 --> 15:28.275
to make contact with Mark Irwin
that night.

15:28.318 --> 15:29.711
- Mm-hmm.

15:31.843 --> 15:34.716
- And?

15:34.759 --> 15:36.283
[knock at door]

15:36.326 --> 15:39.112
- I'm sorry to interrupt,
need to borrow Detective Upton.

15:39.155 --> 15:42.202
We got a break in the case.

15:42.245 --> 15:44.595
- Of course.

15:44.639 --> 15:46.597
We'll talk more
when you get a chance.

15:46.641 --> 15:47.903
- Great.

15:47.947 --> 15:54.779
♪

15:54.823 --> 15:56.781
Doesn't look good,
pulling me out like that.

15:56.825 --> 15:59.306
- Trying to make a murder.

15:59.349 --> 16:01.612
And it can't look bad if you're
keeping steady in there.

16:01.656 --> 16:04.789
Are you?
- Yeah, I am.

16:04.833 --> 16:06.139
- Where are we?

16:06.182 --> 16:07.749
- Santiago's alibi checks out,

16:07.792 --> 16:09.142
but we got another hit.

16:09.185 --> 16:10.926
- I found a camera
on the block.

16:10.970 --> 16:14.408
- This right here is 21 minutes
before the 911 call.

16:15.975 --> 16:18.890
- Thin, young, Hispanic,
like Harvey Clarke said.

16:18.934 --> 16:20.196
- Yeah,
we found him on the sisters'

16:20.240 --> 16:21.458
Snap and Instagram accounts.

16:21.502 --> 16:22.633
It's a clear match.

16:22.677 --> 16:25.680
Name is Rodrigo De Leîn, 16.

16:25.723 --> 16:29.292
Goes to Drake High.
Looks like Candace's boyfriend.

16:29.336 --> 16:31.338
- Scoop him up.

16:35.342 --> 16:37.561
- So you know Candace
and Darlene Clarke?

16:37.605 --> 16:39.259
- Yeah. Known 'em forever.

16:39.302 --> 16:42.001
Is that bad?
- Depends.

16:42.044 --> 16:43.959
When was the last time
you were at their house?

16:45.482 --> 16:48.268
- Day before yesterday.
Picked 'em up for school.

16:48.311 --> 16:49.878
- Yeah, well, now it is bad.

16:52.533 --> 16:54.883
That's yesterday morning,
outside their house.

16:56.885 --> 16:59.235
21 minutes later,
somebody walked inside

16:59.279 --> 17:01.803
and murdered their father.

17:01.846 --> 17:06.286
- And you think I--no.

17:06.329 --> 17:08.636
- Then why are you
lying to us, Rodrigo?

17:08.679 --> 17:09.898
- Because I wasn't supposed
to be there.

17:09.941 --> 17:11.639
- Why?
- I don't know.

17:13.293 --> 17:14.946
- You don't know?
- No!

17:14.990 --> 17:17.514
I pick 'em up every morning,
ever since I got my license,

17:17.558 --> 17:19.516
but the night before,
they called.

17:19.560 --> 17:22.650
They told me not to come,
but I went anyway.

17:22.693 --> 17:24.739
I had to see Candace.
I just--

17:26.958 --> 17:29.004
I like her, and...

17:29.048 --> 17:30.484
I went
and I knocked on the door,

17:30.527 --> 17:31.528
and they told me to go away.

17:31.572 --> 17:32.529
They told me not to come in.

17:32.573 --> 17:33.530
- You keep saying they.

17:33.574 --> 17:35.228
Who's "they"?
- Darlene.

17:35.271 --> 17:37.360
- Yesterday morning,
who told you not

17:37.404 --> 17:39.449
to come inside the house?

17:39.493 --> 17:41.234
- Darlene.

17:41.277 --> 17:44.237
[suspenseful music]

17:44.280 --> 17:45.934
♪

17:49.068 --> 17:49.416
.

17:49.459 --> 17:51.548
- Darlene just ran upstairs
to get a sweater.

17:51.592 --> 17:54.247
- I'm here, Grandma.

17:54.290 --> 17:58.686
- The girls have been
through so much.

17:58.729 --> 18:00.035
- It's okay, Grandma.

18:00.079 --> 18:02.472
We got to help 'em
find the man who did this.

18:03.778 --> 18:04.953
- Thank you.

18:06.868 --> 18:08.739
Candace, um,

18:08.783 --> 18:10.567
your father said that when
the man broke into the house,

18:10.611 --> 18:12.352
he used the side door.

18:12.395 --> 18:14.354
Would that door
have been locked?

18:16.965 --> 18:20.577
- Dad always taught us to lock
the doors, coming and going.

18:20.621 --> 18:23.537
- Okay, so Candace,
you were in the kitchen.

18:23.580 --> 18:25.495
You must've heard
the man break in then, right?

18:25.539 --> 18:27.541
I mean, it's a big, heavy door.

18:30.457 --> 18:32.850
- I heard it.
It was a big crash.

18:34.896 --> 18:37.290
- What about Rodrigo?

18:37.333 --> 18:39.901
- Rodrigo? What about him?

18:39.944 --> 18:41.772
- Well, we talked to him.

18:41.816 --> 18:43.774
He says he came to the house
that morning,

18:43.818 --> 18:47.343
but that, Darlene,
you told him to go away.

18:47.387 --> 18:50.564
But you told us you had already
gone to school at that point.

18:50.607 --> 18:53.306
[suspenseful music]

18:53.349 --> 18:55.612
- People think
we sound the same.

18:55.656 --> 18:58.006
- Well, why would you tell him
to leave in the first place?

19:01.749 --> 19:03.098
- Hmm.

19:03.142 --> 19:05.796
Darlene, would you show us
your arms, please?

19:07.015 --> 19:08.147
- Why?

19:08.190 --> 19:10.149
- Is that a problem?

19:10.192 --> 19:17.330
♪

19:18.940 --> 19:21.072
Both arms, please.

19:36.958 --> 19:39.439
She claims she's been cutting.
- Hmm.

19:39.482 --> 19:41.528
- But I've known plenty
of cutters.

19:41.571 --> 19:43.138
I know what "hesitation cuts"
look like.

19:43.182 --> 19:44.966
They're shallow,
clustered together.

19:45.009 --> 19:46.402
- And this isn't that?

19:46.446 --> 19:48.361
- No, these are knife wounds.
- Huh.

19:48.404 --> 19:50.014
- And the warrant on the house
gave us nothing.

19:50.058 --> 19:52.756
No murder weapon,
no diaries, no computer.

19:52.800 --> 19:55.411
No motive of any kind,
so if these girls had something

19:55.455 --> 19:56.717
to do with it,
we don't have it yet.

19:56.760 --> 19:59.546
- Or they're covering
for someone.

19:59.589 --> 20:01.069
- All right,
let's get two holding cells,

20:01.112 --> 20:04.420
get child advocates down here
to monitor.

20:04.464 --> 20:07.684
We'll put the girls on ice
for the night.

20:07.728 --> 20:11.035
Then we'll separate 'em.
See who cracks.

20:11.079 --> 20:16.867
♪

20:20.915 --> 20:22.917
- I got another call
from my FBI contact.

20:22.960 --> 20:24.223
- Okay.

20:24.266 --> 20:26.660
- Walker North is ambitious
as hell.

20:26.703 --> 20:27.791
- Hmm.
- He wants to run

20:27.835 --> 20:30.185
the Chicago office someday.

20:30.229 --> 20:32.143
- Yeah, but he needs
a scalp first, right?

20:32.187 --> 20:34.537
- A copper's scalp,
what they all want.

20:34.581 --> 20:38.976
Hank, North wasn't
assigned this case.

20:39.020 --> 20:40.108
He asked for it.

20:44.504 --> 20:46.201
- There we go.

20:46.245 --> 20:47.724
Carmela Quintana.

20:47.768 --> 20:50.597
- Well, let's see
if your gut's right.

20:50.640 --> 20:56.124
♪

20:56.167 --> 20:58.561
Carmela Quintana? FBI.

20:58.605 --> 21:00.215
I had a couple of questions
for you.

21:08.005 --> 21:10.530
Yeah,
she already talked to North.

21:10.573 --> 21:12.096
- And what'd she say?

21:12.140 --> 21:15.099
- That Mark Irwin,
when he took her hostage,

21:15.143 --> 21:18.581
said the CPD murdered
Roy Walton.

21:18.625 --> 21:21.628
And that when Upton came
into the room,

21:21.671 --> 21:23.543
she promised Irwin
that she would

21:23.586 --> 21:25.153
"tell the world what happened."

21:26.807 --> 21:27.895
- Seconds later--

21:27.938 --> 21:30.593
- Intelligence killed
Mark Irwin.

21:34.641 --> 21:36.164
- [sighs]

21:38.514 --> 21:41.474
[tense music]

21:41.517 --> 21:48.002
♪

22:55.025 --> 22:57.637
- I assume those are FBI bugs.
- Yeah.

22:57.680 --> 22:59.943
They have a tracker
on the car too.

23:02.076 --> 23:04.295
We are gonna leave them
exactly where I found them.

23:04.339 --> 23:06.385
We just wait for this
to blow over.

23:06.428 --> 23:08.038
- What, so that's the plan?
We're gonna wait for the FBI

23:08.082 --> 23:09.866
to stop caring that you put
a guy in the ground?

23:09.910 --> 23:12.303
- Listen, we are in this now.

23:12.347 --> 23:14.871
- Yeah, exactly.
We're in this.

23:14.915 --> 23:18.048
So you need to tell me
what the feds actually have.

23:18.092 --> 23:21.617
- Everything.
All the loose ends.

23:21.661 --> 23:23.967
But Jay, everything they have
is circumstantial,

23:24.011 --> 23:27.275
and they're missing one thing--
a body.

23:27.318 --> 23:29.233
They can't even say
Roy Walton is dead.

23:29.277 --> 23:30.974
- Oh, they're sure as hell
gonna try.

23:31.018 --> 23:32.933
- You're damn right.

23:32.976 --> 23:35.065
And they are coming
after Hailey.

23:35.109 --> 23:38.329
So we need to hold the line,

23:38.373 --> 23:40.027
'cause one of us cracks...

23:41.289 --> 23:43.247
This whole thing comes down.

23:43.291 --> 23:50.298
♪

23:58.132 --> 23:58.349
.

23:58.393 --> 24:00.656
- Hey. I've been calling you.

24:00.700 --> 24:03.703
[tense music]

24:03.746 --> 24:10.753
♪

24:13.800 --> 24:17.456
- Voight found a tracker
on your car.

24:17.499 --> 24:18.718
And bugs too.

24:18.761 --> 24:21.503
I don't know
if the house is bugged.

24:21.547 --> 24:23.374
You're the FBI's target.

24:23.418 --> 24:26.682
They have way more than they
are telling us that they do.

24:26.726 --> 24:29.816
You're gonna be interviewed
again under oath.

24:29.859 --> 24:31.382
This is all gonna be on you.

24:38.433 --> 24:40.740
- [sighs]

24:45.527 --> 24:47.529
Do you think I should
turn myself in?

24:48.574 --> 24:50.401
- No.

24:50.445 --> 24:52.752
I want to start my marriage
with the woman that I love

24:52.795 --> 24:54.536
out of prison.

24:55.711 --> 24:57.583
- We're supposed
to be together forever.

25:00.324 --> 25:02.196
But if you feel
what I've done is so terrible

25:02.239 --> 25:04.111
there's no coming back,

25:04.154 --> 25:06.592
forever feels like
a real long time.

25:21.824 --> 25:23.826
- Hey, Candace.

25:25.872 --> 25:27.395
- Hi, Darlene.

25:35.316 --> 25:37.623
- So how did you get
to school the morning

25:37.666 --> 25:39.450
that your father died?

25:39.494 --> 25:41.757
- I walked.

25:41.801 --> 25:43.716
- It was two miles, Darlene.

25:45.282 --> 25:47.154
- When Rodrigo came over,
that wasn't you

25:47.197 --> 25:49.504
talking to him
through the door.

25:49.548 --> 25:53.247
Darlene was there.
She hadn't left for school yet.

25:53.290 --> 25:56.903
- We talked
to the marching band director.

25:56.946 --> 25:59.209
He says you didn't show up
for practice that day.

25:59.253 --> 26:02.169
[suspenseful music]

26:02.212 --> 26:04.432
- Darlene already told us
she didn't make it to school

26:04.475 --> 26:05.694
in time for band practice.

26:05.738 --> 26:07.783
- Why would you lie about that?

26:07.827 --> 26:11.308
- I--I don't know.

26:11.352 --> 26:13.659
- You don't know?
- I don't know.

26:14.834 --> 26:16.183
- I think you do know.

26:17.837 --> 26:19.229
- You didn't hear
someone crash

26:19.273 --> 26:20.666
into the house that day,
did you?

26:20.709 --> 26:22.493
- [sniffling]
- No one else came at all.

26:25.975 --> 26:27.194
This was you.

26:29.675 --> 26:31.198
You and your sister.

26:33.548 --> 26:35.594
You did this.

26:35.637 --> 26:38.858
- [sobbing]

26:38.901 --> 26:40.424
Darlene, she was j--

26:40.468 --> 26:43.297
she was just trying
to protect me

26:43.340 --> 26:44.559
from him.

26:44.603 --> 26:47.693
- Your father, he hurt her?

26:50.739 --> 26:52.828
- [sniffles]

26:55.614 --> 26:57.441
So bad.

27:02.751 --> 27:05.972
- Candace, I'm so sorry.
- [crying]

27:06.015 --> 27:11.630
♪

27:11.673 --> 27:13.806
- The wounds on your arm,
they're from a knife.

27:18.854 --> 27:20.290
So you did this?

27:24.599 --> 27:27.646
You killed your father
to end your sister's pain?

27:30.823 --> 27:35.001
Darlene, come on.
The truth.

27:36.785 --> 27:39.527
Darlene.
- [sobbing]

27:39.570 --> 27:41.529
You're right.

27:41.572 --> 27:42.661
- About what?

27:45.881 --> 27:47.622
- I did it, okay?

27:49.842 --> 27:52.932
I took a knife
from the kitchen,

27:52.975 --> 27:54.803
and I waited
until his back was turned,

27:54.847 --> 27:57.023
and I did it.

27:57.066 --> 27:58.677
I killed him.

27:58.720 --> 28:05.684
♪

28:06.641 --> 28:09.731
- Full confession.
- I don't know.

28:09.775 --> 28:13.039
Doesn't feel right.
[knock at door]

28:13.082 --> 28:14.954
- North is ready for you.

28:16.477 --> 28:19.436
[tense music]

28:19.480 --> 28:23.092
♪

28:23.136 --> 28:25.312
- You're aware
this'll be recorded?

28:25.355 --> 28:26.356
- Mm-hmm.

28:27.967 --> 28:30.099
- This is Special Agent
Walker North.

28:30.143 --> 28:32.319
[elevator dings]
Time is 10:12 a.m.

28:34.582 --> 28:38.499
State your full name.
- Hailey Anne Upton.

28:38.542 --> 28:40.457
- Detective, you're aware
of the penalty associated

28:40.501 --> 28:41.807
with making a false statement

28:41.850 --> 28:43.765
to an agent
of the federal government?

28:43.809 --> 28:45.636
- Mm-hmm.

28:45.680 --> 28:46.768
- Day after
Roy Walton disappeared,

28:46.812 --> 28:48.509
you entered the authorized
uniform shop

28:48.552 --> 28:50.467
and bought yourself new BDUs.

28:50.511 --> 28:51.599
Why?

28:54.820 --> 28:56.691
What happened to the old ones?

28:59.520 --> 29:01.957
Paid in cash. Why?

29:07.571 --> 29:09.965
Mark Irwin told
Carmela Quintana

29:10.009 --> 29:12.533
that CPD murdered Roy Walton.

29:14.535 --> 29:16.798
Quintana also swears
that when you got there,

29:16.842 --> 29:21.498
you promised Mark Irwin to
"tell the world what happened."

29:24.632 --> 29:26.068
So what happened?

29:30.420 --> 29:33.684
Men have hurt you.
- Excuse me?

29:33.728 --> 29:35.034
- Starting
with your own father.

29:37.427 --> 29:40.822
- What?
- You know what men do.

29:40.866 --> 29:42.998
You've seen it your whole life.

29:43.042 --> 29:45.609
You saw what Roy Walton did.

29:45.653 --> 29:48.177
You're the one who found those
girls slaughtered like cattle.

29:48.221 --> 29:49.831
You got one other woman
on your team,

29:49.875 --> 29:51.006
you saw what he did to her.

29:51.050 --> 29:52.660
He left her to die
on a concrete floor.

29:54.575 --> 29:58.013
You fight for people
who can't fight for themselves.

29:59.754 --> 30:00.886
And that's what you did here.

30:03.540 --> 30:06.108
Roy Walton's dead,
that's what I think.

30:06.152 --> 30:07.109
You covered it up.

30:07.153 --> 30:11.766
♪

30:11.810 --> 30:13.768
In some ways, I get it.

30:15.814 --> 30:17.859
I admire it.

30:17.903 --> 30:20.035
But...

30:20.079 --> 30:21.515
it's still a crime.

30:24.692 --> 30:29.784
You talk now, I will protect
you the best that I can.

30:29.828 --> 30:31.612
You keep stonewalling me--

30:33.788 --> 30:35.137
- There's a lot of truth
in there, Agent North.

30:37.923 --> 30:39.925
But you don't have a case.

30:43.058 --> 30:46.192
I bought new BDUs
because real cops get dirty.

30:46.235 --> 30:48.237
I made that promise
to Mark Irwin

30:48.281 --> 30:50.239
because he had a gun pointed
to a civilian's head,

30:50.283 --> 30:52.154
and that's what he wanted
to hear in that moment.

30:52.198 --> 30:54.548
That's textbook police work.

30:54.591 --> 30:56.115
I hope Roy Walton is dead.

30:56.158 --> 30:57.638
If you're right about that,

30:57.681 --> 30:59.074
Walton's turning
into dirt somewhere

30:59.118 --> 31:02.512
and everyone's where they're
supposed to be.

31:02.556 --> 31:04.906
So since I'm very obviously
not under arrest,

31:04.950 --> 31:07.778
I'm going back to work now.

31:07.822 --> 31:09.563
I'm a great cop.

31:09.606 --> 31:11.739
I'm in the middle
of working a murder,

31:11.782 --> 31:13.872
and you're wasting
my goddamn time.

31:13.915 --> 31:20.879
♪

31:39.332 --> 31:39.767
.

31:39.810 --> 31:42.074
- Voight was right.
Feds don't have it.

31:42.117 --> 31:44.598
But something's wrong.
- What do you mean?

31:44.641 --> 31:46.905
North?
- No, our case.

31:48.341 --> 31:49.733
- Well, we're charging Darlene.

31:49.777 --> 31:50.778
We're getting ready
to send Candace home.

31:50.821 --> 31:52.258
I think we're done.
- No.

31:52.301 --> 31:54.869
This whole narrative with
the father hurting Candace,

31:54.913 --> 31:56.349
it doesn't fit
with what we know to be true.

31:56.392 --> 31:58.220
Abuse cases,
we know where to look.

31:58.264 --> 32:03.008
But DCFS, CPD, the school
system, we got nothing.

32:03.051 --> 32:07.186
This whole thing feels wrong.
These girls feel wrong.

32:13.061 --> 32:15.107
- What do you got?

32:15.150 --> 32:16.978
- They knew we were
watching them.

32:17.022 --> 32:18.240
They put on a show.
- Good.

32:18.284 --> 32:19.981
- Candace conducted
the whole thing.

32:20.025 --> 32:22.070
Here, watch.

32:22.114 --> 32:24.246
- Right, okay, so this
is when we first put 'em

32:24.290 --> 32:26.640
in the box, right, this is
before they're separated.

32:26.683 --> 32:28.250
The girls haven't
eaten all day,

32:28.294 --> 32:29.991
and they're saying they're
too sick over what happened.

32:30.035 --> 32:30.992
- Mm.

32:32.341 --> 32:36.041
- But here, Darlene's hungry.
So she reaches for a sandwich.

32:36.084 --> 32:39.740
Candace stops her.
We enhanced the sound.

32:41.133 --> 32:44.179
- No. Not yet.

32:44.223 --> 32:45.833
- Okay.

32:47.835 --> 32:49.315
Now look, right there.
- Mm-hmm.

32:49.358 --> 32:50.794
- Candace took a barrette
out of her hair,

32:50.838 --> 32:52.971
and she passed it to Darlene.

32:53.014 --> 32:56.931
- Darlene uses it
to scratch her own arm.

32:56.975 --> 32:59.151
They had to fuel this myth
that Darlene's a cutter.

32:59.194 --> 33:01.196
It's the only way
to explain the cuts on her arm.

33:02.981 --> 33:05.157
- There.
Darlene's not crying anymore.

33:05.200 --> 33:07.986
Candace won't stand for it.
- So Candace pinches her.

33:08.029 --> 33:09.857
This whole thing,
it's a script.

33:11.337 --> 33:14.122
- [sniffling]

33:14.166 --> 33:15.819
- I'm gonna take
another crack at Darlene,

33:15.863 --> 33:18.126
see if I can get her
to tell me the truth.

33:18.170 --> 33:21.173
[suspenseful music]

33:21.216 --> 33:23.827
♪

33:23.871 --> 33:25.133
Glad you got a little
more time together,

33:25.177 --> 33:27.092
but it's time.

33:32.140 --> 33:34.142
Darlene, while we understand
why this happened,

33:34.186 --> 33:38.320
it did happen,
so we got to get you booked up

33:38.364 --> 33:40.061
and let the justice system
do its work.

33:40.105 --> 33:43.238
And it will do its work.
We'll make sure of that.

33:43.282 --> 33:44.718
Let's go.

33:50.071 --> 33:51.464
- Be strong.

33:55.120 --> 33:56.164
I love you.

33:59.385 --> 34:00.864
- Candace, someone will
be coming to take you

34:00.908 --> 34:02.214
to your grandmother's house.

34:04.520 --> 34:07.871
We're gonna make one
more stop before we go, okay?

34:07.915 --> 34:14.922
♪

34:18.491 --> 34:21.363
- [breathing shakily]
- I know.

34:21.407 --> 34:23.061
I'm sorry.

34:23.104 --> 34:26.455
- Can we go then?
- No.

34:26.499 --> 34:28.196
Not until you
tell me the truth.

34:30.285 --> 34:31.895
- I did.

34:33.419 --> 34:36.161
- Most of the blood here
is your dad's.

34:36.204 --> 34:37.901
But the rest of it is
from somebody closely

34:37.945 --> 34:39.425
related to him.

34:39.468 --> 34:42.167
- Yeah. It was mine, okay?

34:42.210 --> 34:44.212
This is where I killed him.

34:44.256 --> 34:47.085
- No, I think this is where
you tried to save him.

34:49.217 --> 34:50.784
- What?

34:55.441 --> 34:57.182
- This is where
you fought off Candace.

34:57.225 --> 34:59.401
You tried to stop her
from hurting your father.

34:59.445 --> 35:03.057
That's how you got those cuts
on your hand.

35:03.101 --> 35:06.016
It wasn't you, Darlene.

35:06.060 --> 35:07.583
- [sobbing]
It was.

35:07.627 --> 35:10.282
I did it.
I told you that I did it.

35:12.284 --> 35:13.937
- I think you've been trying
to keep things together

35:13.981 --> 35:15.939
in this house for a long time.

35:18.551 --> 35:22.424
- I'm tired. I'm so tired.

35:22.468 --> 35:24.209
I confessed, please.

35:26.036 --> 35:30.432
- It's okay.
Can you tell me what happened?

35:30.476 --> 35:31.564
Please?

35:31.607 --> 35:37.265
♪

35:37.309 --> 35:42.052
- She said she was gonna
kill him for a long time.

35:44.185 --> 35:47.536
He was terrified of her.

35:47.580 --> 35:50.409
We both were.

35:50.452 --> 35:54.500
But he loved her too much
to do anything about it,

35:54.543 --> 36:00.897
to ask for help, to get meds,
to put her someplace.

36:00.941 --> 36:03.857
- That's why you even covered
for her afterwards.

36:06.990 --> 36:08.862
- Candace fought me off.

36:11.038 --> 36:15.651
And when she saw I had cuts
on my arms, she threw a fit.

36:15.695 --> 36:17.349
- She planned the whole thing.

36:18.524 --> 36:21.570
- And I messed it up.

36:21.614 --> 36:26.575
She had me take the knife,
our clothes, everything,

36:26.619 --> 36:29.535
and dump it all,

36:29.578 --> 36:32.929
and go to school.

36:32.973 --> 36:36.019
And if I didn't--

36:36.063 --> 36:38.544
if our story didn't add up,

36:38.587 --> 36:41.242
then she--she was gonna--

36:41.286 --> 36:43.679
- She was gonna hurt you too.

36:43.723 --> 36:46.900
- [sobbing]

36:49.163 --> 36:52.122
- Darlene, would your dad
ever hurt you or Candace?

36:52.166 --> 36:55.952
- God, no.

36:55.996 --> 36:58.955
He'd never lay a hand on us.
He loved us so much.

37:01.262 --> 37:03.221
Please--

37:03.264 --> 37:06.267
Please don't let her hurt me.

37:06.311 --> 37:10.053
Please, please.
- It's okay, it's okay.

37:10.097 --> 37:12.926
It's gonna be okay. It's okay.

37:12.969 --> 37:17.409
♪

37:17.452 --> 37:18.627
- Candace.

37:18.671 --> 37:21.369
Candace, tell them that--
that isn't true!

37:21.413 --> 37:23.371
Sweetheart,
I know that you would

37:23.415 --> 37:25.068
never do anything like this!

37:25.112 --> 37:27.027
- Why,
if your father never hurt you?

37:27.070 --> 37:28.550
- I don't know what you're
talking about.

37:28.594 --> 37:30.509
- You just wanted to know
what it felt like.

37:34.077 --> 37:35.557
- Grandma, Grandma, please!

37:35.601 --> 37:37.559
Grandma, I--
I really didn't do anything!

37:37.603 --> 37:39.300
Please, please!
I didn't do anything!

37:39.344 --> 37:41.955
Please, Grandma! Grandma!

37:41.998 --> 37:43.435
[muffled sobbing]

37:43.478 --> 37:45.567
Grandma, please.

37:45.611 --> 37:48.614
I didn't do anything.
Grandma.

37:48.657 --> 37:50.442
[phone buzzes]

37:53.053 --> 37:54.097
- Hey.
- Hey.

37:54.141 --> 37:55.316
Candace is booked.

37:55.360 --> 37:56.622
She's not going anywhere
for a long time.

37:58.406 --> 38:00.278
- Can you come home to me now,
please?

38:00.321 --> 38:01.496
- That's all I want.

38:04.325 --> 38:07.241
Look, we're gonna be okay.

38:09.722 --> 38:12.072
I love you.

38:12.115 --> 38:13.987
- I love you too.

38:18.383 --> 38:20.210
- [sighs]

38:30.612 --> 38:33.746
[siren blares]

38:33.789 --> 38:35.313
You got to be kidding.

38:47.629 --> 38:49.283
- Hey, pal.
- North.

38:49.327 --> 38:52.634
- Follow me.
I want to show you something.

38:52.678 --> 38:56.029
[tense music]

38:56.072 --> 39:03.079
♪

39:31.325 --> 39:33.066
Know who that is?

39:35.547 --> 39:37.549
Of course you do.

39:37.592 --> 39:39.202
You're the one who led me here.

39:41.466 --> 39:43.076
You're the one
who ran Voight's GPS

39:43.119 --> 39:45.121
the night Roy Walton
disappeared.

39:49.822 --> 39:51.345
Damn good police work,

39:51.389 --> 39:52.433
which is either tragic
or ironic.

39:52.477 --> 39:53.608
I'm not sure which.

39:55.567 --> 39:57.264
[chuckles]

39:57.307 --> 39:59.266
I've been searching
for the fault lines

39:59.309 --> 40:01.268
in this whole thing,
trying to find my way in.

40:01.311 --> 40:03.444
And it's you.

40:03.488 --> 40:05.751
It was always you.

40:05.794 --> 40:07.230
- Is that right?
I'm your weakest link?

40:07.274 --> 40:09.319
- No.

40:09.363 --> 40:12.105
No, it's not weakness.

40:12.148 --> 40:14.847
It's decency.

40:14.890 --> 40:16.457
It's possible, Jay,
that you're too good

40:16.501 --> 40:19.591
for this world we operate in.

40:19.634 --> 40:21.331
[sighs]

40:23.551 --> 40:27.120
You truly love Hailey Upton,
don't you?

40:27.163 --> 40:30.428
You had to protect her.
You had to fall in line.

40:30.471 --> 40:33.169
And in the process,
you became a full partner

40:33.213 --> 40:35.607
in the cover-up of a crime.

40:38.914 --> 40:41.221
So here's what's gonna happen.

40:42.875 --> 40:44.442
I'm gonna give you a choice.

40:46.182 --> 40:49.447
Option one,
I arrest you and Hailey.

40:49.490 --> 40:51.405
I promise you,
I will make the case.

40:53.625 --> 40:56.497
Or option two,

40:56.541 --> 40:59.413
you help me take down
the man I really want...

41:02.372 --> 41:04.940
Hank Voight.

41:04.984 --> 41:09.336
♪

41:16.343 --> 41:19.302
[dramatic music]

41:19.346 --> 41:26.353
♪

41:46.373 --> 41:49.376
[wolf howls]
